ndrerit orci et quam commodo feugiat. Aenean sollicitudin eros placerat ligula ornare semper. Duis et neque ac purus ultrices vulputate sit amet nec sem. Proin non tempor nulla. Fusce purus ligula, interdum sit amet felis sed, posuere sagittis nulla. Nulla euismod elit ligula, ac posuere augue commodo non. Morbi tellus ligula, ultrices non tortor.</p>',
                'post_excerpt' => 'Swap clothes with your friends. Crazy thought, right? But really. Think about it. Sometimes you’re sick of wearing something while your best friend has been secretly eyeing that top for years, waiting for you to be done with it. Try it out. Gather a group of friends, a couple of bottles of wine, and start turning trash into treasure.
                But it doesn’t stop there. Get this! These swaps don’t have to just be with your friends. If you’re totally over not only your own closet, but also the closets of everyone else that you know, you can find local clothing swaps in your area.
                The ground rules are simple: Everyone brings a bag or two (or ten!) of stuff they no longer want, you go through and take whatever you like, and any leftovers at the end get donated to charity.
                I happen to be extremely intrigued by this one offered right here in San Francisco that promises to pamper you first and let you swap second.',
